CWP No. 2743 of 2012
Date of Decision : 15.2.2012
Maghar Singh
.... Petitioner
Versus
State of Punjab and others
.... Respondents
CORAM:
HON'BLE MR. JUSTICE PARAMJEET SINGH
Present:-
Mr. Kehar Singh Hissowal, Advocate, for the petitioner.
PARAMJEET SINGH, J. (ORAL)
Learned counsel for the petitioner, after arguing for some time,
states that petitioner has already made representations dated 9.11.2011 and
.11.2011 (Annexures-P-5 and P-6) before the authorities concerned,
which are still pending before it. Therefore, he wants to withdraw the
present writ petition with liberty to pursue his remedy before the
authorities concerned. 
Dismissed as withdrawn with liberty aforesaid.
The authorities are directed to pass appropriate orders on the
aforesaid representations (Annexures P-5 & P-6) within three months from
the date of receipt of certified copy of this order.
(PARAMJEET SINGH)
 JUDGE
